<h1>Learn about hamsters</h1>
<h2>Syrian Hamsters</h2>
<h3>These hamsters have been called golden hamsters because of their coloring. These hamsters have been found in Syria and southern Turkey. These hamsters were discoverd in the early 1800's. The mass of these hamsters as adults is 3-5.3 oz. These hamsters have expanpable cheeks that extend from their cheeeks to shoulders. These hamsters can't eat Choclate, Tomato leaves, Uncooked kidney beans, Almonds, Garlic and more. These hamsters make very good pets. The reason why these hamsters make very good pets is they are the best species for handiling, you don
t need to give them a bath, they don't need freinds and they will not bite you. </h3>
<h3>Veiw quiz on Hannah Hamster School Website</h3>
<h2> Campbells Dwarf Hamster </h2>
<h3> These hamsters don't always like to be held and they live in Inner Mongolia and Northeastern China. They need hight quality crumpled paper and they meed 450 square inches. They are 3.6 inches long and eat dry grains and nuts. They eat 5-7% fat. This hamster is not in threat and breading season in Mongolia starts in April. This hamster is in the Phodopus campbelli family. This hamster can be a pet.</h3>
<h3>Veiw quiz on Hannah Hamster School Website</h3>
<h2>Chinese Hamster</h2>
<h3>This hamster costs 20 dollars. This hamster is very good at climbing and is known for it, you can use toilet paper for bedding. This hamster does not have that much smell, the hamster eats grasses, leaves, shoots, nuts and more. These hamsters normally can not live together.</h3>
